Forums : Help to run simple batch files
This page last changed on Nov 25, 2012 by iloveautomation.

I just started with Openremote and I think the opportunities are endless. Great piece of software. However I am getting stuck trying to run a simple batch file. I followed the steps in http://www.openremote.org/display/docs/OpenRemote+2.0+How+To+-+Execute+Shell+commands but for some reason it does not execute the batch file.
I am running on Win 7 64bit VMWare VM.

I am not sure what to put in additional command box, etc. Any help will be appreciated.

Comments:

"Additional Command" is to add any command line parameters which need to be added to the command.
If you just want to call a plain batch file eg. "/home/marcus/test.sh", just put the full path into the first field and nothing else.
